@NODE intro "Introduction"
AmiMUS is a multi user system for the AMIGA. It combines a password
protection, a meny system and a letter system. Although the letter system
is a bit weak in the currenct version:) 

AmiMUS is, I think, very easy both to use and install. You point and click
all your configurations and then the program does most of the work itself. 

New versions of AmiMUS aren't extremly rare (check out the version history)
and you can always find the latest public available version (Free DL) at:

Reset In Progres, RIP
+46-35-135233
28k8, Amiga

CALL! CALL! CALL! 

And when you're calling to RIP, don't forget to join up in the 
Assassin-online-game. Only press O, wait a second and press 7...
@ENDNODE

@NODE inst "Installation"
I havn't tested AmiMUS on a diskdrive but I guess it would work out ok. It
shure does on a HD.

To install AmiMUS, just doubleclick the icon InstallAmiMUS2.1.  It
req's the C= Installer utility, which is not included in this
package but if you don't already use it you can get it from almost
any Amiga BBS...

If you have used version 2.0-2.02 and would like to use your configs with
version 2.1 you first have to run the AmiMUSConverter20-21 program. This
tool converts config files for version 2.0-2.02 to the format used by
2.1... If you force 2.1 to read old config files it won't work properly.
@ENDNODE
